title: Home and car shot at, Manatee Sheriff's Office reports
content: MANATEE COUNTY - No one was injured when a home where three adults and five children were living was fired upon Sunday night, the Manatee County Sheriff's Office reports. According to a Sheriff's Office news release, a person or persons shot at the unoccupied vehicle and a home in the 400 block of 33rd Avenue East at about 10 p.m. Sunday. The home's residents, three adults in their 20s and 30s and five children 8 and younger, were not hurt.
